snippet.textDisplay: One Twix, many Twix. I think it´s a word play on twig and mix or something similar. Because they look like twigs and they are a mix of chocolate, crackers and caramel. And I´m pretty sure Twix had an other name in the 90´s, but I don´t remember what. I´ve now googled it, and Twix was called Raider up until the year 1991 in most countries, but it wasn´t until 2000 that it officially changed all over the world.
